{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C2494 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2494 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[597,617],"content":"Compiler Error C2494","linkify":"Compiler Error C2494","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2494","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"'keyword' cannot be called from within a filter expression or __finally/finally block","pos":[618,703]},{"pos":[710,769],"content":"You cannot use <ph id=\"ph1\">`keyword`</ph> in a <ph id=\"ph2\">`__finally`</ph> or finally block.","source":"You cannot use `keyword` in a `__finally` or finally block."},{"content":"The following sample generates C2494:","pos":[776,813]},{"pos":[1027,1068],"content":"C2494 can also occur when using <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>/clr<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","source":"C2494 can also occur when using **/clr**."}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C2494 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C2494\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C2494\"\nms.assetid: 5dfd07ab-351d-49c9-b54e-f0a104776ab8\ncaps.latest.revision: 9\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C2494\n'keyword' cannot be called from within a filter expression or __finally/finally block  \n  \n You cannot use `keyword` in a `__finally` or finally block.  \n  \n The following sample generates C2494:  \n  \n```  \n// C2494.cpp  \n#include <malloc.h>  \n  \nint main() {  \n   __try {}  \n   __except ( _alloca(100), 1 ) {}   // C2494  \n   __try {}  \n   __finally {  \n      _alloca(100);   // C2494  \n   }  \n}  \n```  \n  \n C2494 can also occur when using **/clr**.  \n  \n```  \n// C2494b.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr  \n#include <malloc.h>  \n  \nint main() {  \n   char * buf;  \n   try {}  \n   catch (char * buf2) {}  \n   finally {  \n      _alloca(100);   // C2494  \n   }  \n}  \n```"}